quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  27,23,"Verily have found a woman ruling over them and she hath been vouchsafed somewhat of everything, and hers is a mighty throne"
  27,24,"I have found her and her people adoring the sun instead of Allah, and the Satan hath made their works fairseeming unto them, and hath barred them from the way, so they are not guided"
  27,25,"So that they adore not Allah who bringeth forth the hidden in the heavens and the earth, and knoweth that which conceal and that which ye make known"
  27,26,"Allah! there is no God but he, the Lord of the Magnificent Throne"
  27,27,"Sulaiman said: we shall see now whether thou hast spoken the truth or whether thou art of the liars"
  27,28,"Go thou with this epistle of mine, and cast it down unto them, and turn aside from them, and see how they return"
  27,29,"She said: O chiefs! verily there hath been cast unto me an honourable epistle"
  27,30,"Verily it is from Sulaiman, and verily it is: in the name of Allah, the Compassionate, the Merciful"
  27,31,"Saying: exalt not yourselves against me, and come unto me submissive"
  27,32,"She said: O chiefs! counsel me in my affair. I am wont not to resolve on any affair until ye are present with me"
  27,33,"They said: we are owners of power and owners of great violence, but the command is with thee; see then whatsoever thou shalt command"
  27,34,"She said: verily the kings, when they enter a City, despoil it, and make the most powerful inhabitants thereof the most abased; so will they do"
  27,35,"So verily I am going to send a present unto them, and see with what answer the envoys come back"